In [[financial modeling]], the '''Carr–Madan formula''' of {{harvs|first1=Peter|last1=Carr|first2=Dilip B.|last2=Madan|year=1999|txt}} shows that the [[analytical solution]] of the [[European option|European]] [[option price]] can be obtained once the explicit form of the [[Characteristic function (probability theory)|characteristic function]] of <math>\log S_t</math>, where <math>S_t</math> is the price of the underlying asset at time <math>t</math>, is available.

==References ==
*{{citation|last1=Carr|first1=Peter|last2=Madan|first2=Dilip B.|year=1999|title=Option valuation using the fast Fourier transform|journal=The Journal of Computational Finance|volume=2|issue=4|pages=61–73}}.
