The '''Sievert integral''', named after [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[medical physicist]] [[Rolf Sievert]], is a [[special function]] commonly encountered in [[radiation transport]] calculations. 

It plays a role in the [[sievert]] (symbol: Sv) unit of ionizing radiation dose in the International System of Units (SI).

==Definition==
: <math> F(x,\theta)=\int_0^\theta {e^{-x\sec(\varphi)}}\,d{\varphi}.</math>

